rComments: She makes students want to go for their 8:30am classes, now that's saying something. If you do poorly on your first exam don't worry, use her feedback and you'll definitely get an A. She also facilitates great class discussions.
Engaged prof and makes the lectues interesting and hands on. Grading isn't objective and marks are skewed. Also, get ready to have your entire grade based primarily off of group work.
Best teacher I had in my Bachelor! Meilleure professeure que j'ai eu durant mon Baccalauréat!

The book is very helpful (in general) but was only used twice in class (one book per project group is enough).  As a tech. rep. I had to direct, film and edit the mandatory group video project for a 6-people group, write a midterm and a final - got an A. Classes (discussion-based) were fun and funny, and the professor very helpful.

She's amazing. There's only one midterm, which is more of a quiz, and a take home exam. She's really funny and engages the class. She's very interesting. I never bought the textbook and got an A+. There's a group video presentation done, and the references are very crucial for your mark. Overall, great prof!
